      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I am so sorry you are feeling this heavy, hollow weight right now. It sounds like the silence in the house is making the absence of him feel even more deafening, like a ghost in the machine of your daily routine. Please know that your feelings of exhaustion and grief are valid, and you don't have to carry this alone.\n\nIf you are feeling like the world is ending or that you can't go on, please reach out to someone who can offer immediate support. You can call or text 988 in the US to reach the Suicide & Crisis Lifeline, or contact your local emergency services. There are people ready to listen and help you find a way through this darkness.\n\nTo answer your question about the weight: it is incredibly hard to carry, but you are not defined by the burden. You are still here, and that matters. Even if it feels like a hollow shell, the parts of you that love and remember him are still real and strong.",
